#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:6
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:9
msgid ""
"This RFC adds `core::hint::bench_black_box` (see [black box](https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/black_box)), an identity function that hints the compiler "
"to be maximally pessimistic in terms of the assumptions about what "
"`bench_black_box` could do."
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:15
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:18
msgid ""
"Due to the constrained nature of synthetic benchmarks, the compiler is often "
"able to perform optimizations that wouldn't otherwise trigger in practice, "
"like completely removing a benchmark if it has no side-effects."
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:22
msgid ""
"Currently, stable Rust users need to introduce expensive operations into "
"their programs to prevent these optimizations. Examples thereof are volatile "
"loads and stores, or calling unknown functions via C FFI. These operations "
"incur overheads that often would not be present in the application the "
"synthetic benchmark is trying to model."
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:28
msgid "Guide-level explanation"
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:31
msgid "`hint::bench_black_box`"
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:33
msgid "The hint:"
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:39
msgid ""
"behaves like the [identity function](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/"
"convert/fn.identity.html): it just returns `x` and has no effects. However, "
"Rust implementations are _encouraged_ to assume that `bench_black_box` can "
"use `x` in any possible valid way that Rust code is allowed to without "
"introducing undefined behavior in the calling code. That is, implementations "
"are encouraged to be maximally pessimistic in terms of optimizations."
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:46
msgid ""
"This property makes `bench_black_box` useful for writing code in which "
"certain optimizations are not desired, but too unreliable when disabling "
"these optimizations is required for correctness."
msgstr ""

