msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:257
msgid "Unresolved questions"
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:260
msgid ""
"`const fn`: it is unclear whether `bench_black_box` should be a `const fn`. "
"If it were, that would hint that it cannot have any side-effects, or that it "
"cannot do anything that `const fn`s cannot do."
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:264
msgid ""
"Naming: during the RFC discussion it was unclear whether `black_box` is the "
"right name for this primitive but we settled on `bench_black_box` for the "
"time being. We should resolve the naming before stabilization."
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:268
msgid ""
"Also, we might want to add other benchmarking hints in the future, like "
"`bench_input` and `bench_output`, so we might want to put all of this into a "
"`bench` sub-module within the `core::hint` module. That might be a good "
"place to explain how the benchmarking hints should be used holistically."
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:274
msgid "Some arguments in favor or against using \"black box\" are that:"
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:275
msgid ""
"pro: [black box](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/black_box) is a common term "
"in computer programming, that conveys that nothing can be assumed about it "
"except for its inputs and outputs. con: [black box](https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/black_box) often hints that the function has no side-effects, but this "
"is not something that can be assumed about this API."
msgstr ""

#: src/2360-bench-black-box.md:279
msgid ""
"con: `_box` has nothing to do with `Box` or `box`\\-syntax, which might be "
"confusing"
msgstr ""

